\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid3105192 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Could you tell me your name and address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Full name? Lilian Annie Irene Pool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 My year of birth was - 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 In Falmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Oh dear. Well I was born in Falmouth and I came to Falmouth for - to Camborne 
- when I was only - eleven weeks old I believe. My mother, you see, they were living in Camborne but she went home to Falmouth when I was born, just for the birth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Where did you live in Camborne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 River Road. Between Penponds and Camborne. That w
as in 1911. Then I came to - we lived at Treswithian when I was a baby. Do you want that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 That's Treswithian near Camborne?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes, the village of Treswithia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2236071\charrsid813743 n, and then - in 19 - I'm not s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 ure exactly when, about 1904 I should think, we went to Penponds, to the farm my father's - well my grandfather's farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 What was that called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
I don't know what it's called, I don't - I don't know what the name of the farm is, it's Higher Penpods the - the farm, and - we lived there until my grandfather died - in 1906, and then the farm was sold up and we came to Barriper Road then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 How long did you live at Baripper Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 'Til 1916. We came into Camborne then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Which part of Camborne?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Basset Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Did you live there long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
Well we lived there then - my father died when we were there and we lived - and mother and I moved from there in 1934, down to a bungalow in Treswithian Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 From there you moved to here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 And then my mother died while were at - Trevean, she died in 1955 and then in 1958 - I - had this bungalow built and came up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Your father was the son of a farmer was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Your actual home was at Treswithian and the move to Penponds was made on account of grandfather needing someone on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 And the move from Penponds to Barripper Road was because the farm was sold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 And the move from Barripper Road to Basset Street, could you tell me why that took place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Well, my father, who was
 Relieving Officer, got the extra job, he was appointed as Registrar of births and deaths, and had to have an office in town, in Camborne, and - we found a house which was suitable to him to have an office in it and - in Basset Street, so we went there in
 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 And you stayed there until 1934?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 That was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 He - he - no, he died in 1925. But we stayed there in Basset Street until 1934. When we went down to a new bungalow - Treswithian Road.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Did you have that bungalow built?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
Well - we - it was a new bungalow but we didn't have it built. We bought - we were the first people to occupy it, but - we didn't have it built.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 You did have this one built?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes, I had this one built - 'cos it got the traffic - we
ll you see the other bungalow was on the main road and the traffic got very - was beginning to build up in 1958 and was getting noisy in the evenings when I was home from school, and I decided - when I saw this was opening up as a building - plots, I deci
ded this would be a nice place to live, and I'm very pleased I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 You were an only child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Well I think he would probably have been about - let's see, thirty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Well he came from Penponds, he was born in Penponds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 On the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Noton the farm, but on a house very close to it, I - pass it very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 You said his occupation was Relieving Officer and Registrar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Was that always his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
Well - no - he was on the farm - when he was a young man, and then the Af - South African war came and he was a very - military minded, he - he loved military life, and he was in the home volunteers. And 
then hew went to the South African war and when he came back he felt he didn't want to go on with farming. And - he then got the job of Relieving Officer. He - he - then he left the farm there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 You were saying he liked the military life, he didn't continue in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
He continued in the Territorials. Well they became the Territorials later you see, and he was always in it, he was in the second war - in the first world war too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Did he do any casual or part time jobs apart from those you've mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 No. No, he was just a Relieving Officer that was all and - in his civilian line.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3105192 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 In his military career he was in charge of the local platoon for the South African war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1142424 LP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 Yes, he took that - group, he was Sergeant then. And then afterwards, when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2236071\charrsid813743 
\endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743  later}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2236071\charrsid813743  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
on, I suppose somewhere round - I can't remember the date exactly but it was before the first world war, he was - L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2236071\charrsid813743 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16601870\charrsid813743 
